
[1]sofa

   SO'FA, n. [probably an oriental word.] An elegant long seat, usually
   with a stuffed bottom. Sofas are variously made. In the United States,
   the frame of stuffed cloth, with a covering of silk, chintz. calico or
   hair-cloth. The sofa of the orientals is a kind of alcove raised half a
   foot above the floor, where visitors of distinction are received. It is
   also a seat by the side of the room covered with a carpet.
